ce:caption.ce:simple-para:
(A) Ratiometric fluorescence response of NCs/CDs probe upon addition of different concentrations of (A) Hg2+ ions from top to bottom: 0, 20, 40, 60, 80, 100, 150, 200, 300, 400, 600, 800, 1000, 1500, and 2000 nM, and (B) Cu2+ ions from top to bottom: 0, 20, 40, 70, 100, 200, 400, 600, and 1000 nM. Insets show the linear calibration ranges of the probe response to ion concentrations. R0
                      and R are ration signal (I640/I420
                     ) in the absence and presence of ions, respectively. Photographs show the ratiometric fluorescence color of the probe in the presence of increasing concentrations of ions. Higher concentrations of probe and ions were used to take these photos.
